  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good NGOs working in the field of children's education in India?",
  "response": "There are numerous reputable non-governmental organizations (NGOs) in India dedicated to enhancing children's education. Here are some of the prominent ones:\n\n1. **Pratham**\n   - **Overview:** One of the largest non-governmental organizations in India, Pratham focuses on improving the quality of education for underprivileged children.\n   - **Key Programs:** Annual Status of Education Report (ASER), Read India, and educational infrastructure development.\n\n2. **Teach For India (TFI)**\n   - **Overview:** TFI recruits recent graduates and professionals to teach in low-income schools for two years, aiming to eliminate educational inequity.\n   - **Key Programs:** Fellowship program, leadership development initiatives, and community engagement.\n\n3. **Akanksha Foundation**\n   - **Overview:** Dedicated to providing quality education to children from low-income communities in urban areas.\n   - **Key Programs:** After-school programs, teacher training, and holistic development activities.\n\n4. **CRY (Child Rights and You)**\n   - **Overview:** Focuses on restoring children's rights, including the right to education, healthcare, and protection from exploitation.\n   - **Key Programs:** Education initiatives, vocational training, and advocacy campaigns.\n\n5. **Bharti Foundation**\n   - **Overview:** The philanthropic arm of Bharti Enterprises, it aims to improve the quality of education in rural India through robust school networks.\n   - **Key Programs:** Satya Bharti School Program, scholarships, and teacher training.\n\n6. **Smile Foundation**\n   - **Overview:** Works towards providing education, healthcare, and livelihood opportunities to underprivileged children and families.\n   - **Key Programs:** Project Smile (education), Happy Schools, and community development initiatives.\n\n7. **Educate Girls**\n   - **Overview:** Focuses on mobilizing communities to ensure that all girls receive and complete quality education.\n   - **Key Programs:** Enrollment campaigns, community mobilization, and gender sensitization.\n\n8. **Room to Read India**\n   - **Overview:** Part of the global Room to Read network, it focuses on literacy and gender equality in education across India.\n   - **Key Programs:** Library development, book publishing, and support for girls' education.\n\n9. **Magic Bus India**\n   - **Overview:** Uses sports and life skills-based mentoring to educate and empower children and youth from marginalized communities.\n   - **Key Programs:** Educational programs, leadership training, and vocational skills development.\n\n10. **Barefoot College**\n    - **Overview:** While primarily focused on sustainable development, Barefoot College includes educational programs that empower rural children with practical skills.\n    - **Key Programs:** Solar engineering, water management, and grassroots education initiatives.\n\n**Note:** This list is not exhaustive, and there are many other NGOs contributing significantly to children's education in India. It's advisable to research each organization further to understand their specific programs, impact, and how you can support their efforts.",
